# AngryBugs

Early-stage iOS game prototype developed with Objective-C and Cocos2d.

## Overview

AngryBugs is an early mobile game project created as part of hands-on work in native iOS development and 2D game mechanics.

The project demonstrates experience with game structure, animation assets, scene management, and user interaction in a native iOS environment.

## Features

- 2D mobile game prototype
- Native iOS implementation
- Sprite-based animations and assets
- Scene and interaction logic
- Early integration with mobile game frameworks

## Tech Stack

- Objective-C
- Cocos2d
- C / C++
- Xcode
- iOS SDK

## Role

Full-cycle development:
- Project architecture
- Gameplay logic implementation
- UI and scene setup
- Asset integration
- Testing and iteration

## Note

This repository represents an early phase of my software engineering career and reflects long-term hands-on experience in mobile development.

